  "text": "Another question we may ask is about the type of the singularities. Are they poles of some order, or are they approximable by a pole of some order? For Lorenz, we know that the psi-series are convergent singular solutions. Although not all singularities are proved to be of that form, a few singularities have been analyzed in extended precision and verified to be psi-series [CITATION_1] . The dominant part in the psi-series is either a pole or a double pole. Thus the success of Padé is not a big surprise.",
